Katja and Claudia, both recovered from eating disorders, opened Germany's first restaurant for anorexics and bulimics.
The establishment provides a safe space for those still sensitive about food.
In Italy, TV ads targeting children with food products contribute to the rise of eating disorders.
Researchers are exploring the use of leptin to treat infertility and eating disorders.
Middle-aged women are also affected by anorexia and bulimia, facing unique challenges.
Therapists struggle to treat these disorders due to their high mortality rate.
The need for more research and better treatment options is evident.
